## CMocka 1.1.7+ false-positive: when group_setup runs ff_dpdk_init, EAL
## init pollutes the lcore TLS path; cmocka_run_group_tests reports a stale
## "still reachable" block from a global initialisation chain that we cannot
## reach to free without a reverse-init path (FU-CB-DPDKIF-NULLGUARD).
##
## We DO NOT suppress definite leaks here -- only "still reachable" or
## "indirectly lost" coming from EAL init. The integration-test scope
## intentionally accepts EAL globals living until process exit.

# Suppress EAL init-time still-reachable / indirect blocks from rte_eal_init
{
   eal_init_still_reachable
   Memcheck:Leak
   match-leak-kinds: reachable,indirect
   ...
   fun:rte_eal_init
}

# Suppress librdkafka-style global registration chains under DPDK PMDs
{
   pmd_init_still_reachable
   Memcheck:Leak
   match-leak-kinds: reachable,indirect
   ...
   fun:rte_eal_init
   fun:ff_dpdk_init
}
